rdf:Description.schema:name: official website

rdf:Description.schema:description: the item is located on the territory of the following administrative entity. Use P276 for specifying locations that are non-administrative places and for items about events. Use P1382 if the item falls only partially into the administrative entity.

rdf:Description.schema:name: Vestfold Museums

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: part of
rdf:Description.schema:name: part of
rdf:Description.schema:description: object of which the subject is a part (if this subject is already part of object A which is a part of object B, then please only make the subject part of object A). Inverse property of "has part" (P527, see also "has parts of the class" (P2670)).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: street address
rdf:Description.schema:name: street address
rdf:Description.schema:description: full street address where subject is located. Include building number, city/locality, post code, but not country. Use also P669 if the street has its own separate item

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Google Knowledge Graph ID
rdf:Description.schema:name: Google Knowledge Graph ID
rdf:Description.schema:description: identifier for Google Knowledge Graph API (starting with "/g/"). IDs starting with "/m/" are Freebase IDs (P646)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: end time
rdf:Description.schema:name: end time
rdf:Description.schema:description: time an item ceases to exist or a statement stops being valid

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: start time
rdf:Description.schema:name: start time
rdf:Description.schema:description: time an event starts, an item begins to exist, or a statement becomes valid
